.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-08-iteration-log.md:80:- **Hypothesis:** Adding `D3DCOMPILE_PACK_MATRIX_ROW_MAJOR (1 << 3 = 0x8)` to the `flags` bitfield at BOTH D3DCompile call sites — `Direct3d11_VertexShaderData.cpp` (VS site) and `Direct3d11_PixelShaderProgramData.cpp` (PS site, the `[[maybe_unused]]` ps_5_0 SPEC R3 compile-time proof helper) — forces HLSL `float4x4` to compile as row-major. Combined with bumping `D3D11_REWRITE_VERSION 13 → 14` at both sites (so the FNV-1a hash in `Direct3d11_ShaderCache::hashSource` invalidates every cached `.cso` blob on next launch), this delivers a clean first-launch shader recompile under the new flag.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-08-iteration-log.md:175:  - `m_texture` is declared as `ComPtr<ID3D11Resource>` at TextureData.h:90 — to inspect the destination format from unlock, query interface to `ID3D11Texture2D` via `ComPtr::As`. Volume textures hit a separate 3D code path and are not BC-typical; safe to short-circuit the pad to the 2D path.
