.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:131:  - Reviewed `Direct3d11_ShaderCache::hashSource` (Plan 11-05) -- confirmed the FNV-1a hash mixes source bytes + defines (Name + Definition strings) but NOT the profile string directly. Iter-3 fixes this by injecting `D3D11_PROFILE` as a define so the profile string participates in the cache key automatically.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:184:  - Verified `Direct3d11_ShaderCache::hashSource` (Plan 11-05) hashes the ORIGINAL source bytes + defines (the include handler runs LATER, during D3DCompile's parse phase, so the rewritten bytes never enter the FNV-1a accumulator). Cache invalidation therefore needs a separate trigger -- a `D3D11_REWRITE_VERSION` define mirroring the Iter-3 `D3D11_PROFILE` define pattern, so future keyword-list changes auto-invalidate stale `.cso` entries.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:239:  - Read `Direct3d11_ShaderCache::hashSource` -- confirmed defines list is hashed via Name + Definition; the `D3D11_REWRITE_VERSION` define introduced in Iter-4 is the established mechanism for forcing mass cache invalidation when a compile-flag change alters the compile output. Bumping `"1"` -> `"2"` carries the BACKWARDS_COMPATIBILITY behavior change into the cache key without needing a new define.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:289:  - Reviewed `Direct3d11_ShaderCache::hashSource` (Plan 11-05) -- defines hashed by Name + Definition. `D3D11_REWRITE_VERSION` is the established mechanism for forcing mass cache invalidation when a compile-flag change alters compile output. Bumping `"2"` -> `"3"` invalidates every cached `.cso` that pre-dates the STRICTNESS removal.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:338:  2. **Call-site coverage:** extract the rewrite logic out of `Direct3d11_CompileIncludeHandler` into a new shared utility (`Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.{h,cpp}`) and call it from BOTH (a) the existing include-handler site (Iter-2/4 path) AND (b) a NEW main-shader-source site inside `Direct3d11_VertexShaderData::compileOrLoad` (immediately before the D3DCompile invocation). The new utility exposes two entry points with different buffer-lifetime semantics:
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:340:     - `applyToMainSource(char const *src, size_t length, std::vector<char> &outVec, char const *diagName)` -- non-owning view; output written into a caller-supplied stack-scoped `std::vector<char>`. The engine retains ownership of the source bytes (`ShaderImplementationPassVertexShader::m_text`).
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:346:  - Read `Direct3d11_CompileIncludeHandler.cpp` Iter-4 rewrite layer: confirmed `applyKeywordRewrite` is a single-pass scanner with two helpers (`computeRewrittenLength` Pass 1 + `emitRewritten` Pass 2) over a `kReservedKeywords[]` table. Clean to extract: pure functions over byte buffers, no class state, no platform-specific dependencies beyond the engine's `DebugFlags.h` for DEBUG_FATAL guards. Refactor target: a new namespace `Direct3d11_HlslRewrite` with two public entry points (one for each call-site lifetime model) plus a shared internal scanner.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:347:  - Read `Direct3d11_VertexShaderData::compileOrLoad`: confirmed the D3DCompile invocation point at `Direct3d11_VertexShaderData.cpp:341-352`. The pre-D3DCompile source-buffer staging point is the cache-miss branch (post-`Direct3d11_ShaderCache::tryLoad` failure); inserting a rewrite call there means the cache key is still computed against the ORIGINAL source bytes (consistent with the include-handler design where the cache hash sees pre-rewrite content + the `D3D11_REWRITE_VERSION` macro). Mass cache invalidation rides along by bumping `D3D11_REWRITE_VERSION` from `"3"` to `"4"`.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:351:  - Confirmed `Direct3d11_ShaderCache::hashSource` mixes both source bytes AND defines list into the FNV-1a 64-bit hash. The `D3D11_REWRITE_VERSION` macro participates in the hash via its Definition string, so bumping the version invalidates every prior `.cso` blob; D3DCompile rebuilds all under the new effective source (after rewrite) and re-stores.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:356:  1. **Commit 1** (`feat`): create `Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.{h,cpp}` -- pure-utility namespace with two entry points (`applyToIncludeBuffer` heap-owning, `applyToMainSource` view+vector). Extract the Iter-4 keyword-rewrite logic from `Direct3d11_CompileIncludeHandler.cpp` (`computeRewrittenLength` / `emitRewritten` / `applyKeywordRewrite`) into the new utility. Add Rule B (`:\s*c\d+\b` -> whitespace) and Rule C (`:\s*register\s*\(\s*c\d+\s*\)` -> whitespace) match helpers (`tryMatchRuleB` / `tryMatchRuleC`). Rule precedence: Rule A tried first (starts at a non-`:` position based on whole-word boundary); at `:` sites Rule C tried before Rule B (Rule C is the more-specific longer match starting at the same `:`, so the longer-match-wins shape avoids Rule B greedily eating the `:` of a Rule-C-eligible site). DEBUG_FATAL overflow guards in `emitRewritten` catch any Pass-1/Pass-2 divergence at the byte-output level. Diagnostic logging via `DEBUG_REPORT_LOG_PRINT` reports rewrite count + size delta per shader. New TU wired into `Direct3d11.vcxproj` + `.filters` under `src\win32`.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:358:     - `Direct3d11_CompileIncludeHandler::Open` -- replace the inline `applyKeywordRewrite` call with `Direct3d11_HlslRewrite::applyToIncludeBuffer`. Same heap-owning semantics + same fast path when no rewrites apply.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:359:     - `Direct3d11_VertexShaderData::compileOrLoad` -- inside the cache-miss branch, before the D3DCompile call, invoke `Direct3d11_HlslRewrite::applyToMainSource(sourceText, sourceLen, rewrittenSource, displayName)`. Replace the D3DCompile `pSrcData` / `SrcDataSize` arguments with `rewrittenSource.data()` / `rewrittenSource.size()`. The vector is stack-scoped to the cache-miss block; the D3DCompile call is synchronous; the vector cleans up after.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:364:  - `MSBuild -t:Direct3d11 -p:Configuration=Debug -p:Platform=Win32` EXIT=0. `gl11_d.dll` 1,411,584 bytes (Iter-6 baseline 1,399,808 bytes; +11,776 bytes for the new Direct3d11_HlslRewrite TU -- the size change reflects the new function bodies + Rule B/C match helpers + new diagnostic logging surface).
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:369:  - **D-13 grep clean:** 20 hits for `D3DPOOL_MANAGED|OnLostDevice|OnResetDevice` in `Direct3d11/`, ALL inside `//` comment lines documenting the invariant. Zero functional uses. The new `Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.h` preamble at line 83 contributes one new D-13 comment hit (per-file boilerplate).
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:372:  - **FFP scan clean:** new TU `Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.cpp` has 0 `#ifdef FFP / D3DTSS_ / D3DTOP_` functional code; modified TUs (`Direct3d11_VertexShaderData.cpp`, `Direct3d11_PixelShaderProgramData.cpp`, `Direct3d11_CompileIncludeHandler.{h,cpp}`) carry no functional FFP code.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:376:- **Semantic-loss caveat recorded (forward-looking):** Rules B and C drop the legacy register-binding metadata. D3DCompile's automatic register-allocator picks registers from the available pool starting at `c0`. If the engine assumes a specific register layout at the C++ level (e.g., `SetVertexShaderConstantF(4, ...)` expecting the shader to read constant `c4` for a transform matrix), runtime rendering could break in subtle ways -- compiles succeed, draws don't FATAL, but produce wrong colors / black geometry / NaN math. Plan 11-07 Task 3 smoke would surface any such visual issue. Suspect list if visuals look wrong: (a) this iteration's semantic-info loss, (b) Iter-5's BACKWARDS_COMPATIBILITY flag changes intrinsic-call output, (c) the 12 X3206 implicit-truncation warnings in `functions.inc` (non-fatal but document lossy float-vector arithmetic that might produce different precision than the D3DX9-era compiler did). The caveat is documented in (1) `Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.h` preamble, (2) `Direct3d11_VertexShaderData::compileOrLoad` Iter-7 comment block above the rewrite call, and (3) this iteration-log entry.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:409:    - `Direct3d11_VertexShaderData.cpp:308-309` -- `Direct3d11_HlslRewrite::applyToMainSource(sourceText, sourceLen, rewrittenSource, displayName);` -- confirmed present + receiving the engine-owned `m_text` view.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:423:- **Root cause:** Iter-7's Rules B/C hardcoded the literal `c` for the register-type letter in both `tryMatchRuleB` and `tryMatchRuleC`. The X3202 site on `2d.vsh(8,44-45)` uses one of the other 4 canonical D3D11 register-type letters (`b` / `s` / `t` / `u`) -- which letter exactly is unknown until the THROWAWAY diagnostic dump reveals the actual line-8 content. The Iter-7 wiring (Direct3d11_HlslRewrite call site in compileOrLoad + REWRITE_VERSION cache invalidation) was correct end-to-end; the defect is purely in the rules' coverage scope.
