.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:579:  2. **Axis 2 (cache invalidation only):** bump `D3D11_REWRITE_VERSION` 6 -> 7 in BOTH VS + PS compile sites. The rewrite-rule behavior is unchanged from Iter-9 (rules still strip `[bcstuv]` register bindings), but the dump blocks only fire inside the cache-miss branch (the rewrite runs INSIDE `if (!Direct3d11_ShaderCache::tryLoad(...))`). Without the version bump, every shader would hit Iter-9's `.cso` cache from a previous launch and the dump blocks would never execute. The bump forces a mass cache miss, fires the dumps on the first applyToMainSource + first applyToIncludeBuffer call, and rebuilds every blob under byte-identical rewrite output. Iter-11's revert + actual fix will bump 7 -> 8.
