.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:716:     - `Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.cpp`: added `sawColonThisLine` parameter to `tryMatchRuleB` and `tryMatchRuleC`. Both matchers now return 0 (no match) when the flag is FALSE. Modified both passes of the scanner (`computeRewrittenLength` + `emitRewritten`) to maintain the flag identically: FALSE at start, TRUE on `:`, FALSE on `\n`. The two passes are guaranteed to agree on the flag's evolution because they walk the same input bytes with identical predicates; the DEBUG_FATAL pass1/pass2 divergence check at function end catches any drift. Updated file-preamble documentation with the Iter-11 line-scoped-state design + the over-strip / X4016 narrative.
