.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-07-iteration-log.md:779:  - Verified by reading `Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.cpp:412-499` (computeRewrittenLength) and `:501-596` (emitRewritten) line-by-line. The two passes evolve the flag identically. The ordering is: try Rule A (which doesn't touch `:`), try Rule C (which reads flag, doesn't mutate on no-match), try Rule B (same), fall through to passthrough (which sets flag on `:` and resets on `\n`). On the FIRST `:` of a line: flag is FALSE going in; Rule C returns 0; Rule B returns 0; passthrough emits the byte and sets flag TRUE. CORRECT on paper.
