.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09-PLAN.md:100:1. **PS NULL color output** -- D3D11 has no implicit fixed-function pass-through PS. Without a bound PS, geometry rasterizes but no fragment writes occur (invisible). Plan 11-05 documented this caveat; the engine ships D3D9 PEXE pixel-shader bytecode which D3D11 CreatePixelShader rejects, so m_d3dPS stays null. **Iter-2 addresses via minimal fallback PS** (~30 lines of HLSL + 15 lines of compile + ms_fallbackPS singleton in Direct3d11_PixelShaderProgramData; applyPreDrawState binds the fallback when m_currentPSData->getPixelShader() returns null).
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09-PLAN.md:109:- StaticShaderData.cpp:820-895 (Pass::apply binds VS via Direct3d9_StateCache::setVertexShader, plus material / textureFactor / alpha-test / fog / stencil / texture stages -- ALL of which Plan 11-09 INITIALLY DEFERS)
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09-PLAN.md:113:- Per-pass VS extraction ONLY in Iter-1. Material / textureFactor / alpha-test / fog / stencil / texture-stage state ALL DEFERRED to later iterations as they surface as visual/correctness symptoms.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09-PLAN.md:146:**Trust boundary recap from Plan 11-07/Plan 11-08:** engine call surface unchanged; no new trust boundaries this plan introduces. The new threat surface is "incorrect VS/PS binding -> wrong geometry rendered" (visible bug, not crash) and "Pass::apply lifetime mismatch -> dangling pointer to ShaderImplementation::Pass data" (CODEX flagged as low-risk per Plan 11-09 Question 4; non-owning pointers like D3D9 mirror is safe). Threat model expansion lands in 11-09-SECURITY.md if smoke surfaces specific concerns.
