.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.15-CODEX-CONSULT-font-atlas-bgra-dxt5-format-mismatch.md:92:   **B.** **Override `destFormat` when mismatch detected on first lock** — if the engine asks for `TF_DXT5` destination but first `lock()` arrives with `TF_ARGB_8888` data, recreate `m_texture` at BGRA8 and the matching SRV. The font atlas burns 4× the GPU memory (256×256 BGRA8 = 256KB vs BC3 = 64KB) but it just works.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.14-PLAN.md:40:      to: "Plan 11-09.14 binds SRV0 + sampler0 in Direct3d11_StaticShaderData::apply() per the D3D9 sibling pattern (Direct3d9_StaticShaderData::Pass::apply + Stage::apply)"
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.14-PLAN.md:54:1. **Select by `m_textureIndex == 0`, not "first iterator."** D3D9 indexes `m_stage[(*i)->m_textureIndex]`; the dynamic fallback PS samples `t0`/`s0` so slot 0 means texture-index 0. If no `TextureSampler` in a pass has `m_textureIndex == 0`, unbind SRV0 (let the PS read 0 from the unbound SRV → magenta/black) rather than guessing with "first entry."
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.14-PLAN.md:62:- **Unbind on absence:** when no `TextureSampler` in a pass has `m_textureIndex == 0`, set `ms_boundSRV[0] = nullptr` to avoid sticky cross-shader bleed. Sampler0 can keep the default (no functional issue) or be set explicitly per resolved data when present.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.14-PLAN.md:63:- **No material work needed.** The dynamic fallback PS reads only `t.Sample(s, input._v0.xy)`. Material/textureFactor/textureScroll/alphaTest/fog flow through cbuffers the fallback PS never reads; they matter only when Phase 12 re-authors real PSes.
