.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.14-iteration-log.md:38:1. **Select by `m_textureIndex == 0`, not "first iterator."** D3D9 indexes `m_stage[(*i)->m_textureIndex]` (Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp:789); the dynamic fallback PS samples `t0`/`s0` so slot 0 means texture-index 0. If no `TextureSampler` in a pass has `m_textureIndex == 0`, unbind SRV0 — fallback-to-first is diagnostic experiment, not correct architecture.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.14-iteration-log.md:47:- **Unbind on absence:** when no `TextureSampler` has `m_textureIndex == 0`, set `ms_boundSRV[0] = nullptr` (avoid sticky cross-shader bleed). Sampler0 default is fine.
