.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.14-CODEX-CONSULT-srv0-per-pass-texture-binding.md:59:- `Stage::construct(StaticShader const &, ShaderImplementation::Pass::PixelShader::TextureSampler const &)` (`.cpp:297+`) extracts `textureSampler.m_textureTag` → `shader.getTextureData(m_textureTag, &textureData)` → `textureData.texture->getGraphicsDataAddress()` → `Direct3d9_TextureData const * const *`. Sampler state (anisotropy, address-mode, filters) comes from the same `TextureData` fields, falling back to `TextureSampler` defaults when the per-instance `textureData.X == TA_invalid` / `TF_invalid`.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.14-CODEX-CONSULT-srv0-per-pass-texture-binding.md:69:**Current D3D11 `StaticShaderData::apply()` body** (cpp:208-248) is unchanged from Plan 11-09 Iter-1. It sets `ms_currentVSData` + `ms_currentPSData` via `Direct3d11_StateCache::setCurrentVSData` / `setCurrentPSData` and returns. Zero SRV/sampler/material/textureFactor/textureScroll/alphaTest/stencil/fog handling. The deferral comment quoted above is verbatim from this site.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.14-CODEX-CONSULT-srv0-per-pass-texture-binding.md:136:The D3D9 sibling at `Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp:787-788` iterates `pass.m_pixelShader->m_textureSamplers` directly. For Bucket A, we'd take just the first entry. Is "first entry" the right diffuse channel, or does the engine encode diffuse vs specular vs normal positionally (slot 0 = diffuse by convention) — i.e. should we check the `TextureSampler.m_textureTag` for a "diffuse" tag pattern instead of position 0?
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.14-CODEX-CONSULT-srv0-per-pass-texture-binding.md:160:### Q5 — Material / textureFactor / textureScroll handling
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.14-CODEX-CONSULT-srv0-per-pass-texture-binding.md:162:D3D9 `Pass::apply()` (cpp:835-924) does extensive cbuffer constant writes for material, textureFactor, textureScroll. Plan 11-09 Iter-2's CODEX consult ("dead-static user-constants") established that the engine writes these via `setVSConstants`/`setPSConstants` which we route through `Direct3d11_StateCache::setVSConstants`/cbuffer slot 0. So material/textureFactor/textureScroll ARE already flowing — just into a cbuffer the dynamic-fallback-PS doesn't read.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.14-CODEX-CONSULT-srv0-per-pass-texture-binding.md:182:**First correction:** bind the sampler whose `m_textureIndex == 0`, not "first iterator." D3D9 constructs stages by destination texture index: `m_stage[(*i)->m_textureIndex]`. The fallback PS samples `t0`/`s0`, so slot 0 means sampler index 0. If no sampler has index 0, unbind SRV0 and use magenta/black behavior rather than guessing. A fallback-to-first is only useful as diagnostic experiment, not correct architecture.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.14-CODEX-CONSULT-srv0-per-pass-texture-binding.md:203:Use `m_textureIndex == 0`. Do not tag-match "diffuse" yet. The engine's pixel-shader sampler model is positional, and D3D9 confirms that by indexing `m_stage` with `m_textureIndex`. Tags resolve *which* texture object feeds that slot; they do not define the slot.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.14-CODEX-CONSULT-srv0-per-pass-texture-binding.md:222:#### Q5 — Material / textureFactor / textureScroll handling
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.13-PLAN.md:45:Replace the hardcoded-magenta fallback PS (Plan 11-09 Iter-2) with a textured-passthrough PS so the world becomes visually recognizable. Plan 11-05 documented PEXE rejection as a "Phase 12 asset re-author" punt: engine ships pre-compiled D3D9 PEXE bytecode in `.psh` IFF chunks (`DWORD * m_exe`), D3D11 `CreatePixelShader` rejects D3D9 bytecode, so 100% of asset shaders end up with `m_d3dPS = null` and Plan 11-09 Iter-2's fallback covers every draw.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.13-iteration-log.md:15:Kenny visual confirmation: "All I saw was magenta triangles, no real terrain was rendered." Plan 11-09.12 audit + fix confirmed the all-magenta state is now ISOLATED from any other artifacts — pure Plan 11-05 PEXE rejection (engine ships pre-compiled D3D9 PEXE bytecode in `.psh` IFF chunks; D3D11 `CreatePixelShader` rejects D3D9 bytecode → `m_d3dPS = NULL` for 100% of asset PSes → Plan 11-09 Iter-2's magenta fallback covers every draw).
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.13-iteration-log.md:96:- `Direct3d11_VertexShaderData.h:113` + `.cpp:547` — `m_reflectedInputs` + `D3DReflect` + `GetInputParameterDesc` block is a clean parallel for the new `m_reflectedOutputs` + `GetOutputParameterDesc` block to mirror.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.13-CODEX-CONSULT-reflection-driven-fallback-variant-selection.md:11:The D3D11 renderer plugin (Phase 11) cannot consume the engine's pre-compiled D3D9 PEXE pixel-shader bytecode (`.psh` IFF assets ship as DWORD * `m_exe` SM 1.x/2.x bytecode; `CreatePixelShader` rejects D3D9 bytecode). Plan 11-05 documented this as a "Phase 12 asset re-author" punt and Plan 11-09 Iter-2 introduced an install-time **magenta fallback PS** that `applyPreDrawState` binds whenever `ms_currentPSData->getPixelShader()` is null — which is 100% of asset draws.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.13-CODEX-CONSULT-reflection-driven-fallback-variant-selection.md:61:- Compile-time per VS: `D3DReflect` the bytecode; capture the input signature (filter SV_*).
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.13-CODEX-CONSULT-reflection-driven-fallback-variant-selection.md:95:- `D3DReflect` the VS output signature.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.13-CODEX-CONSULT-reflection-driven-fallback-variant-selection.md:110:- `D3DReflect` the VS output signature.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.13-CODEX-CONSULT-reflection-driven-fallback-variant-selection.md:111:- If the VS does NOT output `TEXCOORD0`, rewrite the VS HLSL source (via `Direct3d11_HlslRewrite`) to add a `float2 texcoord0 : TEXCOORD0;` output to the VS output struct, zero-initialized in the VS body.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.13-CODEX-CONSULT-reflection-driven-fallback-variant-selection.md:118:**Cons:** modifying VS source is invasive. The Plan 11-09.8 input-side phantom works because the INPUT layout is plugin-side data structure (we control it); the OUTPUT signature is *baked into the VS bytecode* — we can't add a phantom output without recompiling the VS itself. That means rewriting the engine VS HLSL source pre-compile, which is fragile (the existing `Direct3d11_HlslRewrite` Rules A-E don't touch struct definitions; would need a Rule G that augments output structs). High implementation cost.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.13-CODEX-CONSULT-reflection-driven-fallback-variant-selection.md:131:- Per-VS reflection at compile-time is already proven by Plan 11-09.8 (`Direct3d11_VertexShaderData::install` already calls `D3DReflect` on the bytecode).
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.13-CODEX-CONSULT-reflection-driven-fallback-variant-selection.md:190:**Q3 — Reflection storage.** Store this on `Direct3d11_VertexShaderData`. That matches the existing `m_reflectedInputs` precedent in `src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_VertexShaderData.h:112` and the current `D3DReflect` site in `src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_VertexShaderData.cpp:547`. I would store a compact reflected-output vector or enum, not only a bool, because the 483K failures already suggest TEXCOORD0 may not exist in the smoke population.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.13-CODEX-CONSULT-reflection-driven-fallback-variant-selection.md:214:- **Reflection precedent verified at `Direct3d11_VertexShaderData.h:113` + `.cpp:547`** — `m_reflectedInputs` plus the `D3DReflect` block that filters `SV_*` system values and captures `SemanticName / SemanticIndex / ComponentMask / ComponentType` is exactly the template to mirror for outputs. Iter-3 adds a parallel `m_reflectedOutputs` populated by the same code path's twin (`reflector->GetOutputParameterDesc`).
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.12-iteration-log.md:29:2. **PEXE-rejection evidence collection.** Plan 11-05 PEXE rejection is the load-bearing cause of all-magenta rendering. The D3D11 debug layer should surface evidence: CreateShader / CreatePixelShader failures with specific HRESULT, PSSetShader-with-null bindings, shader-bytecode-fingerprint mismatches, etc. That evidence becomes Plan 11-11's entry point.
.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.12-AUDIT.md:113:The debug-layer log shows **zero** errors directly attributable to Plan 11-05's PEXE rejection (no `CreatePixelShader failed`, no `PSSetShader with null PS`, no `Invalid shader bytecode`).
