.planning\phases\11-d3d11-renderer-plugin\11-09.15-CODEX-CONSULT-iter42v2-postparity-particles-depth-sky-RESPONSES.md:89:> 1. **Q1 blend-state model:** the "D3D9 conditionally applies blend factors" hypothesis is probably wrong. D3D9 constructs `m_alphaBlendSource`, `m_alphaBlendDestination`, and `m_alphaBlendOperation` for every pass, then applies every recorded render state in `Pass::apply()`. The blend enum mapping is direct. Also, `ShaderImplementationPass` initializes blend fields, so "uninitialized/zero blend fields" is unlikely.
